TITLE: Defining Git Subcommand Structure in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates the structure for defining a git subcommand in JavaScript. It includes properties for the command name, usage, description, arguments, and an execute function that handles the command's logic.
SOURCE: https://github.com/HeyPuter/puter/blob/main/src/git/README.md#2025-04-06_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
export default {
    name: 'help',
    usage: [
        'git help [-a|--all]',
        'git help <command>',
    ],
    description: `Display help information for git itself, or a subcommand.`,
    args: {
        allowPositionals: true,
        options: {
            all: {
                description: 'List all available subcommands.',
                type: 'boolean',
            }
        },
    },
    execute: async (ctx) => {
        ctx = {
            io: {
                stdout,
                stderr,
            },
            fs,
            args,
            env,
        }
    }
}
```

