TITLE: Defining share-intent Type-Tagged Object Structure in Puter
DESCRIPTION: Defines the structure of a share-intent object used in the /share endpoint. This object is used to apply permissions to existing users and can be transformed into a token:share for email sharing purposes, which is then stored in the share database table.
SOURCE: https://github.com/HeyPuter/puter/blob/main/src/backend/doc/lists-of-things/list-of-tto-types.md#2025-04-06_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: markdown
CODE:
```
### `{ $: 'share-intent' }`

- Used in the `/share` endpoint
- Permissions get applied to existing users
- For email shares, is trasnformed into a `token:share`
  which is stored in the `share` database table.

- **variants:**
  - `share-intent:file`
  - `share-intent:app`
- **properties:**
  - `permissions` - a list of permissions to grant
```

